list.comment: Comfort Zone, a short film focused on @jonathansiegrist’s and my training this winter, is now live. Link in profile. @tarakerzhner did a great job of showing our preparation for sport climbing. @joe_segreti photo of one of the other routes I tried to do during my spring training but ultimately failed in. Always room for improvement... thanks @lasportivana for making it all happen.

This is what it looks like to rappel in on El Cap - @jimmy_chin navigating a total junk show on his way down for a day of work on the wall. It was his birthday yesterday - happy birthday, Jimmy! After 10 years of climbing and shooting together it’s still always a pleasure.
We’re all continuing to tour with Free Solo this week. I was in Seattle last night and Portland tonight - pretty cool to see the film spreading around the country. But starting to look forward to touching real rock again.... @freesolofilm @natgeo @thenorthface @cheynelempe photo.

The folks at @reelrock shared this fun clip of @cedarwright climbing with me in Antarctica last winter that’s part of this year’s film tour. I haven’t gotten to see all the other films yet but I’m looking forward to seeing @adam.ondra flash 5.15 and all the competitive speed climbing. Find your local Reel Rock screening to get your dose of climbing inspiration (if the other two feature films that came out recently weren’t enough...). Also, Cedar has been asking me to go back to Antarctica on a self supported Sufferfest3 style expedition. Good idea or bad idea?!

Inspecting my gear on the way up El Cap... @jimmy_chin photo from the film Free Solo. It’s been a wild ride all over the country for the last few weeks - huge thanks to everyone who’s already come out to see the film. For those asking about screenings in specific cities (or Europe, or Canada, etc) - be patient, it’s expanding each week. And eventually it’ll be on TV and streaming online. But it’s definitely way better to see on the biggest screen possible - you have to do El Cap justice!

Just had my first date with the Diamond! After over 20 years of climbing I finally got on CO’s finest alpine granite. And to make it memorable I biked from Boulder and scrambled the Casual Route. Glorious day in the mountains (though I felt a bit rugged from the altitude). My real lesson from the day is that I’m never destined to be a road biker or trail runner - gotta stick to climbing...

Speed climbing is all about moving smoothly and efficiently. Both of which are easier when you have a partner that you deeply trust. Thanks, @tommycaldwell for always making good decisions (and also being very quick). You’re the man! That’s why our shoes are named after you! Pic: @samuelcrossley

So stoked to be in Telluride, CO for the Telluride Film Festival. Excited that Free Solo is premiering today, but more excited that there’s so much good climbing in town! So nice to be in the mountains.

I’ve had an amazing time at the Telluride Film Festival. The Free Solo premier was surprisingly powerful and seeing how the film affected audiences was inspiring.
And the outdoor recreation opportunities around Telluride kept it all pretty fun! The whole crew got to go adventuring on the via ferrata - one of the highlights for sure.
The journey continues at the Toronto International Film Festival this week - probably more gym time and fewer mountains...

In the spirit of Veterans Day it seems appropriate to share this video of 5 blind veterans kayaking down the Grand Canyon. (I have to add, the idea of running huge rapids blind seems really scary.) This is a trailer - the full 5 minute film is linked in bio. I found it surprisingly moving. It’s a good reminder of the healing power of the outdoors.

I’m sweepstaking off a day of climbing with me in Yosemite to support the @honnoldfoundation! Or hiking/adventuring if you don’t want to climb. But you can win all the gear you need and a fun day in Yosemite at the link in bio or:
www.omaze.com/alex
There’s still a chance to join me for a day of adventuring in Yosemite - all levels welcome, climbing or hiking or anything else. Support the @honnoldfoundation and enter at: omaze.com/Alex

Super stoked to see The Dawn Wall in theaters soon! @tommycaldwell has always been a huge inspiration and seeing him and @kjorgeson climb possibly the hardest bigwall in the world together is pretty darn exciting. It’s opening in New York and LA on the 14th and then appearing as a one night event in theaters all over the country on the 19th. I’ve heard that tickets are selling out so get yours soon. It’s a great film, stoked for everyone involved. @senderfilms @brettlowell @joshlowell
And yes, I know it’s confusing timing that there are two different feature films coming out about climbing on El Cap at almost the same time. When it rains it pours. So much psyche!

Pretty honored to make the cover of the @adventuresportsjournal! As a Sacramento native it’s nice to be recognized by a magazine that’s been around Northern California for almost 20 years. And in a more general sense, I’ve been really humbled by the reception to Free Solo this weekend - it’s really been powerful to see how it affects audiences. Free soloing is such a personal pursuit, it’s interesting to share it on a big screen. I’m really grateful that Chai Vasarhelyi (@mochinyc) and @jimmy_chin did such a great job crafting the film. Check Freesolofilm.com for screenings (link in bio). And don’t worry, more are constantly being added. It’ll eventually be everywhere.

Big congrats to @bradgobright and Jim Reynolds (@chimney_jim) for climbing Mt Watkins, El Cap, and Half Dome in a day!! And it was Brad’s birthday! No better way to celebrate a birthday than doing so much climbing in a day that you feel 100 years old for the next week...
I got this photo of @tedhesser shooting the two big wall masters on top of Watkins as we all hiked up to the road. Beautiful sunset. And super proud effort by Jim and Brad. Congrats on the Triple!!

I’m pretty excited about two new products from @blackdiamond that are supporting the @honnoldfoundation. They’ve released the Freerider chalk bag (the same bag I used on the actual climb, and signed), and a new, signed version of the classic Solution harness. They’re both products that I’ve used forever so I’m happy to promote them. But more importantly I’m glad that a percentage of sales go to the @honnoldfoundation. Thanks! Link to the gear in bio.

El Capitan in all it’s glory! Stoked to be coming back to Yosemite for a few days this week. Free Solo will be showing at the Yosemite Facelift on Tuesday! The premier in NYC this week was great, but screening the film in Yosemite will be extra special - I’m hoping that it will be a good way to say thank you to all the climbers and members of the Park Service who helped along the way.
But mostly I’m just excited to be back in the most beautiful place on earth... @jimmy_chin photo. @natgeo #freesolo

Happy birthday to the one and only @tommycaldwell !! I happen to be giving a slideshow in his hometown of Estes Park today and I’ve decided to make it entirely about adventures we’ve had together. Dug up this photo from our first real day of climbing together - free climbing the Triple in Yosemite in 2012. It was a pretty awesome start to a great partnership. @benjaminbditto photo.
Cave life. Love being home for a minute. A rare @sannimccandless belay picture.

Sunrise on top of the Freerider - @jimmy_chin got this picture of me dropping in on El Cap for a long day of rappelling and working moves.
Free Solo expands into another 100 theaters across the country this weekend in cities including Seattle (I’ll be there!), San Francisco, Portland(and there!), Atlanta, Austin, Saint Louis, Miami and many more. For more details or a theater near you check out:
www.freesolofilm.com

I wanted to post something scary for Halloween - this was the best I could find on my phone. The opening move of the Boulder Problem on Freerider - courtesy of the remote cameras for @freesolofilm.
Free Solo is still showing in hundreds of theaters across the country. It should open in Europe sometime in the next month or so. UK in December I think. It’s been a pretty wild ride so far.
I hope everyone’s enjoying a lovely Halloween!
I just did a podcast with All Things Climbing about the origins of the @honnoldfoundation and the work we’ve been supporting. Link in bio for a nice long chat.

Tomorrow is my birthday! I’ve never really liked gifts, and I don’t need much, but last year my girlfriend’s family started what will hopefully be a tradition of donating to the @honnoldfoundation for my birthday. And that’s something I can appreciate. So for anyone who wants to get me a birthday present or wish me well, please consider setting up a recurring donation at the link in bio.
Any amount is appreciated - and every amount has an impact. Depending on where you live, $6 can buy you a cup of coffee or a couple tacos. But for a family living in rural Malawi, $6 can buy a solar lantern - a lantern that can provide free, sustainable light, and replace the old kerosene lamp that filled their house with a toxic black cloud.
Use the link in my bio to set up any kind of donation. Thanks.
@tedhesser photo from an expedition to Kenya.
Sometimes I still get to climb outside! Took advantage of a relatively cold and windy day to go scrambling on some south facing black varnish. Stoked to be home, even if it’s only for a day.

Free Solo got accepted into the Toronto International Film Festival! Pretty excited to go to #TIFF18 in a few weeks. And more excited to see the film in theaters at the end of September. Link to the film trailer in my bio - for those that haven’t seen it. And pretty stoked about the movie poster - nice pic @jimmy_chin. @natgeo @thompowers1 @freesolofilm

I gave a TED talk earlier this year - it’s now available online (link in bio). I contrasted my experiences free soloing Half Dome and El Cap as a way to talk about the value of preparation and training. It was probably the most gripped I’ve ever been while giving a talk so don’t judge too harshly - the TED conference is pretty intimidating, especially for a rock climber... Enjoy!

Pretty excited to see this year’s Reel Rock film tour - 4 films, including my expedition to Antarctica with @thenorthface last year. But most importantly there’s video of @adam.ondra climbing 5.15 first try which seems totally outrageous. Check out: Reelrocktour.com for tickets and showtimes. @reelrock premiers Nov 1st and has 500+ showing around the world - get psyched! Such a wealth of climbing media this year.

@cannonjtc and I just climbed the double - my first time climbing El Cap and Half Dome in a day (yes, I’ve done the Triple twice, but never the double. Actually as I wrote that I realized that I soloed the double in 2010. So this is my first double with a partner - sounds less cool). Anyway, Jordan made a fun little story about our day, check out @cannonjtc for the adventure.
This is my new strategy - let my partners shoot things so I never have to...
Thanks @samuelcrossley for the summit pic with the afternoon’s objective in the background.
I think this wraps up my Valley season - too hot now and time to move on. Lots of ups and downs this season; Yosemite is always giving and taking away. Lots to think about.

I’ve had an amazing weekend at the inaugural @outwild.co festival. It’s been a great break from film touring to spend a weekend in beautiful mountains with such caring and engaged people. One of the big themes of Outwild has been focusing on values and using them to lead a more intentional life - it’s been a good reminder for me to just post about the things that I truly care about. I guess the weekend has helped me tap back into some of my idealism. Along those lines - take advantage of a beautiful Sunday to go early vote (unless you’ve already voted by mail). Elections matter - help govern. (We voted last week in NV, my first time doing so physically after a decade of voting by mail in CA. Pretty exciting.)

I’m so stoked to announce the release of FREE SOLO, the film documenting my free solo of El Cap last year. It’s co-directed by my friends Chai Vasarheyli (@mochinyc) and @jimmy_chin and will be in theaters this fall. Get psyched! #FreeSolo @freesolofilm

What a day in Patagonia!! It feels slightly criminal to not be taking full advantage of a weather window like this for climbing. But hiking is lovely too... I’m on a quick visit through El Chalten for a symposium with Wilderness Travel before rejoining the Free Solo movie tour madness. I’d almost forgotten how much I love just being beneath inspiring mountains... so stoked for the next time I get to climb here...

It’s your last chance to win a day of climbing with me in Yosemite! Climb, hike, or just picnic in El Cap meadow - your choice. And most importantly, it supports the @honnoldfoundation. I know I’ve posted this several times already - don’t worry this is actually the last day. And it’s raised more money for the foundation than I’ve ever been able to give directly. So thanks for the support.
Enter through my bio link or: omaze.com/yosemite

Toronto International Film Festival highlights: looking all classy with @sannimccandless, seeing my Canadian godfather Peter again after too many years, and sampling the various climbing gyms around Toronto. And of course, seeing #freesolo on a huge screen. El Cap felt life size! The whole film premier whirlwind continues! @freesolofilm

Pretty excited to hear that Free Solo has won the People’s Choice Award at the Toronto International Film Festival. But I’m even more excited that now that the film is being released I can finally see all the pictures that @jimmy_chin has shot with me over the last few years of film making. I never got to see any of the material while we were shooting - seeing it now is a nice way to revisit two years of great climbing. This is a shot of Freestone, a route that, as the old guide book said, is probably harder than Astroman (despite being shorter). And being up there with Yosemite Falls raging behind definitely adds to the ambiance. Gotta love Yosemite! @natgeo @mochinyc
And for anyone curious: @freesolofilm opens in theaters September 28th. Get psyched!

Tom Frost - what an inspiration. Visionary climber and photographer (and gear tinkerer), but more importantly a genuine, kind, and positive man.
He came up to the Valley for moral support when @hansflorine and I set the speed record on the Nose in 2012. He joked that while us shaving 9 minutes or so off the record was impressive, it paled in comparison to the 40 odd days that he shaved off the record on the second ascent.
One of the highlights of last fall was doing an interview with Tom in El Cap Meadow for an upcoming documentary about his life from Flatlander Films. To hear his account of the first ascent of the Salathe while looking up at the wall was truly inspiring. Thanks, Tom.

I’m going to be speaking/participating at the inaugural @outwild.co festival in Malibu, CA this November 2-4. The festival is focused around spending more time outside and leading a more values-driven life. Come join the party - link in profile. And early bird tickets are $100 off for another 2 days. Get psyched. @honngy photo.

Very pleased to announce my partnership with @beyondmeat! I’ve been a vegetarian for 5 or 6 years because I considered it the easiest way to minimize my environmental impact. I think it’s fitting that Beyond Meat uses the tag line “the Future of Protein” because I genuinely believe that making meat directly from vegetable protein is the way of the future. Why use an animal as a grossly inefficient middleman when it’s possible to make meat directly from a plant without having to butcher another creature?! The Beyond Burger tastes and feels like an old school beef burger but with a tiny fraction of the environmental impact and none of the cruelty. Basically, I’m honored to partner with Beyond Meat because I hope that they’re shaping the future. A cleaner, lower impact way to eat - definitely the future. #gobeyond #futureofproteinambassador

I don’t think I’ve ever posted specifically about @chaivasarhelyi and all the incredible work she put into crafting Free Solo. Chai technically co-directed the film with @jimmy_chin - but everyone knows how much time Jimmy likes to spend skiing... Chai’s the powerhouse who actually did the hard work of crafting the film. @freesolofilm is still in theaters all over the country (just got a text from a laggard aunt of mine who’s just getting around to seeing it). Still time to appreciate Chai’s hard work.
